<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-05-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="531" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">741.83/5–1447: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Durbrow</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-05-14">May 14,
                                1947</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1772. May 6 [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>]. <hi rend="italic">Pravda</hi>
                            May 14 carries following Tass denial: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Tass is authorized to state report of Cairo paper <hi rend="italic">Al-Ahram</hi> to effect that in Stalin’s
                                    conversation with Bevin Soviet Govt promised not to support
                                    Egypt in UN, does not correspond to facts.</p>
                                <p>“Conversation did not touch upon question of UN, or of support or
                                    non-support by USSR of any Egyptian demand in UN.</p>
                                <pb facs="0789" n="775" xml:id="pg_775"/>
                                <p>“It was stated with regard to relations between Britain and Egypt
                                    that this was affair of Britain and Egypt, and USSR, in
                                    accordance with its unchanged policy of non-intervention, does
                                    not think of intervening in this matter.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Durbrow</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>